  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>tofu</strong> into 12 <span class=\"text-danger\">[24]</span> slices</p><p>Combine 2/3 of the <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>in a large bowl, add the <strong>tofu slices</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside to marinade</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-tofu-katsu-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of<strong> cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Add the <strong>marinated tofu</strong> to a baking tray with any <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> from the bowl, sprinkle over the<strong> black sesame seeds </strong>and <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and crisp – this is your <strong>sesame-crusted tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-tofu-katsu-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Heat a small, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>curry powder </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-tofu-katsu-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, transfer to a small bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>mango chutney</strong>, <strong>reserved soy sauce </strong>and 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>katsu dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-tofu-katsu-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and peel the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-tofu-katsu-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the<strong> blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Once the rice is cooked, add the <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> to the pot and cook for a further 1 min or until warmed through then drain</p><p>Wash the<strong> baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-tofu-katsu-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>carrot ribbons </strong>and <strong>baby leaf salad</strong> to the pot with the cooled brown rice & edamame</p><p>Add the <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and gently mix everything together – this is your <strong>brown rice & edamame salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-tofu-katsu-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sesame-crusted tofu</strong> over the <strong>brown rice & edamame salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>katsu dressing </strong>all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
